# Feature 6 — Review & Revision Flow

## Goal
Once a designer saves and submits a copy request from the new request page,
the Copy Team can review the generated copy string by string, leave per-item 
comments, and submit their review. The request detail page shows different 
views based on the user's role.

## Request Statuses
- draft → saved but not submitted, only visible to designer
- submitted → designer submitted, waiting for Copy Team review
- in_review → Copy Team has opened the request
- approved → Copy Team approved all copy strings
- changes_requested → Copy Team left comments on one or more strings

## Status Labels (shown in UI)
- draft → "Draft"
- submitted → "Submitted for review"
- in_review → "In review"
- approved → "Approved"
- changes_requested → "Changes requested"

## Designer Flow
- Designer clicks "Save & Submit for review" on the new request page
- Status changes to "submitted"
- Designer is redirected to the request detail page in read-only mode
- Designer can see their selected EN and AR copy per annotation (read-only)
- Designer sees status badge "Submitted for review"
- If status is "changes_requested":
  - Each copy string that has a comment shows the reviewer's comment 
    in a highlighted yellow box below that string
  - Designer can update their copy selections per string and resubmit
  - Each resubmission creates a new version in version history
- Designer NEVER sees "Approve" or "Request changes" buttons
- Designer NEVER sees a "Generate copy" button on the detail page

## Copy Team Flow
- Copy Team dashboard shows all submitted/in_review requests
- Copy Team opens a request → status automatically changes to "in_review"
- Copy Team reviews each copy string individually
- For each copy string, reviewer can:
  - Mark as approved (green checkmark toggle per string)
  - Leave a comment/revision note on that specific string (text input)
- Once done reviewing all strings, reviewer clicks "Submit review"
- Status logic after submit:
  - If all strings are approved → status changes to "approved"
  - If any string has a comment → status changes to "changes_requested"
- Designer is notified either way
- Copy Team NEVER sees "Generate copy" button

## Role-based Request Detail Page
The request detail page (/dashboard/[id]) must show different UI based on role:

DESIGNER VIEW:
- Request title, feature context, tone shown at the top
- Screenshots displayed as reference (read-only, scrollable)
- Each annotation shown as an individual card:
  - Annotation label + type badge
  - Selected EN copy (LTR, read-only)
  - Selected AR copy (RTL, dir="rtl", read-only)
  - If status is "changes_requested" and string has a comment:
    show reviewer's comment in a #FFEA00 highlighted box
    and allow designer to update their selection for that string
- Status badge at the top
- Resubmit button (only if status is "changes_requested")
- No generate, approve, or submit review buttons

COPY TEAM VIEW:
- Request title, feature context, tone shown at the top
- Screenshots displayed as reference (read-only, scrollable)
- Each annotation shown as an individual card containing:
  - Annotation label + type badge
  - Designer's selected EN copy (LTR)
  - Designer's selected AR copy (RTL, dir="rtl")
  - Approve toggle (green checkmark) per string
  - Comment field per string (text input, optional)
- "Submit review" button at the bottom 
  (primary CTA: #FFEA00 background, #222629 text)
- No "Approve all", "Request changes", or "Generate copy" buttons

## Notifications
- In-app notification badge on the nav showing unread count
- Notification types:
  - "Your request [title] has been approved"
  - "Your request [title] needs changes"
  - "New request [title] submitted for review" (for Copy Team)
- Notifications stored in Firestore under notifications/{userId}
- Mark as read when clicked

## Data Structure
Request document updates:
- status (updated throughout flow)
- reviewedBy (Copy Team user ID)
- reviewedAt (timestamp)
- selectedCopy (Designer's selected copy per annotation)
- stringReviews: array of { annotationId, approved, comment } 
  (per-string review data from Copy Team)
- versionHistory (array of previous submissions)

## UI
- Status badges:
  - draft → #F4F5F6 background, #222629 text
  - submitted → #FFEA00 background, #222629 text
  - in_review → blue background, white text
  - approved → green background, white text
  - changes_requested → red background, white text
- Reviewer comments shown in #FFEA00 highlighted box per string
- Notification bell icon in nav with unread count badge
- Mobile friendly